Default event functions are pre-defined functions in Maplestory Worlds that can be used to create events. Here are some common default event functions:

#### 1. `OnStart()`

This function is called when the event starts.

```lua
function OnStart()
    -- Event start logic here
end
```

#### 2. `OnEnd()`

This function is called when the event ends.

```lua
function OnEnd()
    -- Event end logic here
end
```

#### 3. `OnPlayerEnter()`

This function is called when a player enters the event area.

```lua
function OnPlayerEnter(player)
    -- Player enter logic here
end
```

#### 4. `OnPlayerLeave()`

This function is called when a player leaves the event area.

```lua
function OnPlayerLeave(player)
    -- Player leave logic here
end
```

#### 5. `OnTimer()`

This function is called at regular intervals.

```lua
function OnTimer(timer)
    -- Timer logic here
end
```

